sentences: The band was formed in 1996 when Dave McDonnell (credited as The Diminisher), Jeremy Barnes (as "Marta Tennae"), and Griffin Rodriguez ("Blue Hawaii") teamed up to write and improvise music.
Their almost-entirely-improvised album In A Different City was recorded in Chicago during this time, and later released in 1999.
The Orange Tapered Moon EP followed in 2000, recorded during a late night marathon session at WFMU.
In 2001, the band released A Flat Inside A Fog, The Cat That Was A Dog, another ambitious project.
In A Different City (CD/LP) - Pickled Egg/Misra -  1999
A Flat Inside A Fog, The Cat That Was A Dog (CD/LP) - Pickled Egg/Misra - 2001
"Chunks Of Syrup Amdist Plain Yoghurt" (7") - Pickled Egg/Contact - 1999
The Orange Tapered Moon - (12"/CD) - Pickled Egg/Misra - 2000
The Orange Tapered Moon EP followed in 2000, recorded during a late night marathon session at WFMU.
Barnes now records as A Hawk and a Hacksaw.
